                                            <input type="checkbox" id="rv-294734" />
                                            <div class="review-content" id="review-content-294734">
                                                <p>Style Score:<br /><br />Author doesn't bother describing... well anything really. Just names things and people. We are introduced to 'characters', who are described as 'female... human' + name and that's still all we know of them many chapters later. Appearance? Garb? such things don't exist in this story. Similiarly no context is given for any locations - you have descriptions like 'descended to next floor / entered a room - found X Enemy Types' than a fight description and good luck to the reader on trying to picture it. Sometimes there aren't even details like whether the encounter is in a hall way, room whatever...<br /><br />We do know however the exact length and thickness of MC's cock and that his hair is waist high. The 'sexual content' tag is kind of misleading as the 'scenes' manage to be less sexual than school biology textbooks. Expect lots of erotic descriptions such as "I shoved my giant cock in her and fucked her for an hour. It was fun. Used XYZ skill to make her orgasm."<br /><br />Story: Frankly the LitRPG level and skills up flow so quickly and inconsistently that it was kind of pointless to keep track. There is no important link between the game system and story progression except to establish right from first chapter that MC is obscenely overpowered, and that the reader shouldn't bother doubting that any fight will be anything other then a curbstomp. <br /><br />He is a powerful mage + overwhelming mind control powers + dual wielding Drizzit-copy and starts the game with custom set of weapons that scale to his level and power. At lvl 1, he takes out lvl 5 creatures without breaking a sweat. At level 7 he soloes parties of NPCs (as in Fighter, Barb, Rogue supported by Cleric and DPS Mage).<br /><br />And the whole thing is happening in a completely static world - for example that 'fucked for an hour' bit I mentioned above? that was to a patrol of a cult preparing for a ritual. "I lifted one leg up over my shoulder, and thrust into her. She screamed, but I kept going." - you immediately get a good gauge of how well though out the setting/story is when the MC can go into a dungeon, attack a patrol on perimeter of a cult that's gettign ready for a critical ritual and rape a screaming cult member for an hour right on the spot where he found them, and no one interrupts them and everone is still surprised when he later tucks his dick in and proceeds deeper into the ruins. <br /><br />Oh and apparently when one is a 'high' level caster class and thinks they have an advantage in spell might over an incubus that just barged in on your ritual, butchered all your followers, admitted to raping one of them, enslaved the second survivor right in front of you and than offer you a wager of a challenge fuck, promising to help you if you outfuck him - well the obvious choice is to accept, let yourself get stripped naked and spell bound. <br /><br />Yep... that is the level of intelligence that the author acribed to MC's enemies - before he even starts using his mind control powers.<br /><br />Grammar score: author put in futas into the story and took the time to invent ridiculous sounding pronoun to refer to them... 'hir' and 'shi' galore. It comes off exactly as stupid sounding and annoying in middle of combat descriptions as one would expect.<br /><br />Tl,DR - System screens can be skipped as there is nothing important to story there, and fight scenes can all be skipped because you know how it ends. The characters aren't characterized beyond name, sex, race, class and the 'gripping story' involves overpowered MC vs. a world chock full of the dumbest NPCs ever written in a LitRPG. <br /><br />Re: 'traumatizing content' tag - there is real edgy stuff here such as impaling women on a magic spit that heals them to make the experience longer lasting. Just for the fun of it - done to a complete stranger he just met, had no particular animosity for or anything to gain from the torture. But it's okay - as even a priestess of the local goddess of Love and Passion doesn't sweat the small stuff like still-living women being roasted on the fire nearby... not when there is this dashing incubus and his giant cock are in view and fade-to-black sex non-scene to be had. <br /><br />In fact, what kind of Goddess of Love and Passion wouldn't rather bless said dashing succubus right on the spot?<br /><br />"The elf maidens were a little discomfited to be eating human flesh" - the maidens in question would be those good aligned priestesses... err sorry - Pincess Priestesses</p>
<p>That should tell you what all the many mentiones of alignment systems and 'potential consequences' might amount to in this world.<br /><br />Only got up to chapter 12 on this one.<br /><br /><br /></p>
