                                            <div class="review-content" id="review-content-70433">
                                                <p>Ever play the old paper &amp; pencil roleplaying games where you got to play the bad guy?\xc2\xa0 That is this story, expect all those\xc2\xa0things you might try and do as the bad guy.</p><p>\xc2\xa0</p><p>While the story and main characters are very good and have some depth to them.\xc2\xa0 There is one main issue I have -</p><p>The story is very good if you read everything at once.\xc2\xa0 As it has a very continuous flow and each chapter builds off of the last chapter.\xc2\xa0 Reading it one chapter every couple of days breaks up the story and gives it a bit of a choppy feeling.</p><p>\xc2\xa0</p><p>Couple people have made posts about the OP nature of the main character.\xc2\xa0 The main character is not OP.\xc2\xa0 He plays to his strengths, does his best to avoid his weakness, and is smart enough to get help (one way or another - remember he's playing on team evil) to cover areas he's not strong in.</p><p>\xc2\xa0</p><p>\xc2\xa0</p>
                                            </div>
