    <div class="portlet-body">
                        <div class="chapter-inner chapter-content">
            Author's Note:<br />So, I've got a post on my blog <a href="http://frozensoulandotherworks.blogspot.com/2016/06/patreon-goals-and-rewards.html" target="_blank">HERE</a>\xc2\xa0where I talk about a few things I'm considering doing, involving both this story, and Frozen Soul. One of the possible rewards includes being able to help create members of Zayn's <del>harem</del>\xc2\xa0party! I've also got a goal for including 'extended editions' of some chapters of both stories, starting with expanding V1, C5 of Frozen Soul, From Russia with Blood.<br /><br /><br /><hr /><br /><br />The next morning, my pets and I had gathered in the Inn\xe2\x80\x99s common room to enjoy a nice breakfast. It was simple fare, just some eggs, bacon, bread with butter, and mead to drink with it. Tasty as hell, though. Too many people go and try to make things \xe2\x80\x98fancy\xe2\x80\x99 and end up overcomplicating things. There\xe2\x80\x99s a time for fancy dishes, but a simple meal can do a lot to help a person\xe2\x80\x99s mood. And I was in a good mood. I found that you get a small amount of XP for performing acts related to your profession. So me training the girls last night gave me a couple hundred XP. Not much, but still something.<br />\xc2\xa0<br />While we were eating, the Princesses came down. I smiled when they came over to my table, and we began chatting about how we\xe2\x80\x99d spent the last couple days. The fact that I\xe2\x80\x99d gotten to rank E in my initial assessment by the guild was impressive to them. I also mentioned that I\xe2\x80\x99d taken a couple quests out towards Wyrmwood, so we\xe2\x80\x99d be able to start moving before too long.<br />\xc2\xa0<br />As for what the priestesses were up to, they had been training, it seemed, so that they could better defend themselves if trouble came up. We agreed to check in with eachother tonight at dinner, but be prepared to leave the city tomorrow, if need be.<br />\xc2\xa0<br />Of course, leaving on a journey isn\xe2\x80\x99t exactly simple. We needed supplies, and preferably transportation. I had considered buying horses, but strong horses, capable of carrying a rider over long distances would not be affordable just yet. But a wagon and a couple draft horses just might be. And then there was the issue of supplies. Food, water, and feed for the animals. Plus, survival gear like tents. Lots of stuff to buy.<br />\xc2\xa0<br />After breakfast, we returned to the marketplace. This time, however, we visited more of the \xe2\x80\x98mundane\xe2\x80\x99 shops. The Princesses would take care of their own supplies, but that still left me with the burden of paying for the rest (after all, any funds my pets had made since I got them went directly to me). Fortunately, I wasn\xe2\x80\x99t without resources. And by resources, I mean a gamer\xe2\x80\x99s ability to sniff out cheats.<br />\xc2\xa0<br />A bit of asking around told me that Brum Farshade and his wife, Airhy, were trying to have a child, but things were \xe2\x80\x98difficult\xe2\x80\x99 since Airhy had been injured early in life. A bit more asking around (and a couple drinks), and I found out that Airhy was actually sweet on this guardsman and had been taking an alchemist\xe2\x80\x99s work to keep from getting pregnant. Now, none of this was my business, but Brum was the guy who ran the stables, and so when I introduced myself as a servant of Sharess, who had come after hearing of his difficulties, I was able to get a discounted price on a pair of draft horses, a wagon, and harnesses, in return for the blessing of the Goddess upon their bed. I cast Fruitful Passion on the husband, and told him that, so long as he lay with his wife, and no other, before the new moon, then he would have the child he sought.<br />\xc2\xa0<br />After that, a trip to the general store was in order. A lot of haggling ensued, and my Negotiation skill went up to Beginner 6. But I managed to get rations and feed for ten days, canteens with water for 4 days (which we could refill along the way), tents, bedrolls, a healthy supply of rope, and other sundry supplies. Honestly, boring stuff.<br />\xc2\xa0<br />Anyways, all the supplies cost me 10 GP. But we\xe2\x80\x99d be ready for pretty much anything that happened. After that, I went to talk to my two contacts for the quests. Hard to deliver goods or escort merchants without speaking face to face, after all.<br />\xc2\xa0<br />I started with Hunter Becket. Becket, as it turned out, was a Halfling, a half-human. Looked like his other half was goblin. He also was missing the better part of his left leg. But whatever. He was most happy to talk to me once I explained I was here about the quest.<br />\xc2\xa0<br /><span style="color: #339933;">\xe2\x80\x9cAh, good! I was supposed to source ten Black Forest Wolf pelts for the leatherworker, but got caught in a storm, and my wagon wrecked. I was barely able to save the furs. Then more wolves attacked me, and I ended up in this state. A merchant brought me to Falon, and now I\xe2\x80\x99m stuck doing chores at the temple until I can save up enough for some healing.\xe2\x80\x9d</span><br />\xc2\xa0<br />After a few mindless pleasantries, I received the 10 furs, and stored them in my inventory.<br />\xc2\xa0<br />Oddly enough, I found Silas Horneby at the slave market. Turns out, he was a traveling slave trader, moving \xe2\x80\x98goods\xe2\x80\x99 from one area to another. We actually had a good chat over lunch in a private room. The guy wasn\xe2\x80\x99t a cruel bastard. Most of the people who were put in his keeping were sold to pay off debts, or because they\xe2\x80\x99d broken some law. He tried to find them good owners, and had actually developed something of a reputation along those lines.<br />\xc2\xa0<br />For my part, I simply told him stories of my adventures back in WoD. The game settings said that Travelers came from another world, so that\xe2\x80\x99s what all the NPCs believed anyways. Made it so I could tell some of my early adventures without drawing too much attention.<br />\xc2\xa0<br />Small talk out of the way, we agreed to move out tomorrow morning.<br />\xc2\xa0<br /><span style="color: #9999ff;">\xe2\x80\x9cI hope things will go smoothly. These bandits on the road lately\xe2\x80\xa6\xe2\x80\x9d</span><br />\xc2\xa0<br /><span style="color: #3366ff;">\xe2\x80\x9cYeah, I heard about them. Are we expecting trouble? More than the usual?\xe2\x80\x9d</span><br />\xc2\xa0<br /><span style="color: #9999ff;">\xe2\x80\x9cWell, one of my cargo is the son of a bandit leader. The little prick was caught trying to raid one of the storehouses here in the city. City leaders want him gone, and they paid me double the normal rate to try and get him elsewhere.\xe2\x80\x9d</span><br />\xc2\xa0<br /><span style="color: #3366ff;">\xe2\x80\x9cAh, so we can definitely expect trouble, then. My pets and I have stocked up on supplies already, so we\xe2\x80\x99ll be ready to go in the morning. Do any of your slaves have combat training? If we come into a tight spot, it\xe2\x80\x99ll be good to know how many blades we can rely on.\xe2\x80\x9d</span><br />\xc2\xa0<br /><span style="color: #9999ff;">\xe2\x80\x9cA couple. But the only one worth talking about is my personal slave, who is practiced in defensive magics.\xe2\x80\x9d</span><br />\xc2\xa0<br /><span style="color: #3366ff;">\xe2\x80\x9cRight. Hopefully we won\xe2\x80\x99t need it, but it is good to know that there\xe2\x80\x99s someone strong behind us, in case we get attacked from both sides. We\xe2\x80\x99ll have to assume that they\xe2\x80\x99ll lay ambushes.\xe2\x80\x9d</span><br />\xc2\xa0<br /><span style="color: #9999ff;">\xe2\x80\x9cYeah. Fortunately, your group aren\xe2\x80\x99t the only guards. There\xe2\x80\x99s another party of adventurers who also accepted the quest.\xe2\x80\x9d</span><br />\xc2\xa0<br /><span style="color: #3366ff;">\xe2\x80\x9cExcellent! Then let us hope that we\xe2\x80\x99ll have enough numbers to keep the bastards\xe2\x80\x99 heads down.\xe2\x80\x9d</span><br />\xc2\xa0<br />After agreeing to meet at the city gates the next morning just after breakfast, we went our separate way. Pets in tow, I headed to the training hall. Why? Because I wanted to grind my skills some more. My Sword skills were already quite good for my level, so I started raising my other masteries, with the Dagger, Whip, and Bow. The others were also working on their weapon skills, even Della. We\xe2\x80\x99re going out into the wild, so we need to be ready for things.<br />\xc2\xa0<br />Honestly, apart from grinding my masteries, the practice was really for Yukiko. From what she had said, she\xe2\x80\x99d been enslaved directly out of the tutorial, and it was only by doing a LOT of service-based quests that she\xe2\x80\x99d managed to get to her current level. So she had no combat experience in this world. And even in WoD, she was a Blacksmith first, and fighter second, so her combat skills needed the work badly.<br />\xc2\xa0<br />Finally, it was about time for dinner, when I had promised that we would meet the Princesses again to discuss our plans. Unfortunately, we weren\xe2\x80\x99t able to return to the inn directly. Why? Because some idiots had noticed my good fortune (three female slaves following a guy around attracts attention), and decided it was their place to make me share the wealth, either by giving them the girls, or paying them with my deep pockets. I used Observe on them, and laughed.<br />\xc2\xa0<br /><div style="max-width: 100%; overflow:auto"><table><tbody><tr><td colspan='4'>Thief<br />Human Male<br />Level 8 Rogue</td></tr></tbody></table></div><br />\xc2\xa0<br />There were seven of those, but the eighth proved to be much more interesting.<br />\xc2\xa0<br /><div style="max-width: 100%; overflow:auto"><table><tbody><tr><td colspan='4'>Zephara Void<br />Half-Elf Female<br />Level 15 Flame Sorceress<br />Title: Chainbreaker<br />Bounty: 500 GP</td></tr></tbody></table></div><br /><br />This wasn\xe2\x80\x99t an NPC leading these goons, but a player! And that Chainbreaker title sounded like the opposite of mine. Probably meant she went around freeing a bunch of slaves. And no doubt killing a bunch of people along the way. No other way a Level 15 gets a 500 GP bounty on them.<br />\xc2\xa0<br />The group tried to cut us off, four ahead and four behind, with the sorceress behind us. Poor bastards. Then this Zephara spoke. <span style="color: #ff9933;">\xe2\x80\x9cSo, this is how it is. You give me the girls, and I\xe2\x80\x99ll make your death quick. You resist, you burn slow. Either way, I\xe2\x80\x99m going to kill a sicko like you for taking slaves.\xe2\x80\x9d</span><br />\xc2\xa0<br />I simply laughed, and said,<span style="color: #3366ff;"> \xe2\x80\x9cOh, really? I\xe2\x80\x99m so going to enjoy this. So tell me, how many innocent slave owners have you killed?\xe2\x80\x9d</span> I didn\xe2\x80\x99t really care. But her talking was convenient to me.<br />\xc2\xa0<br /><span style="color: #ff9933;">\xe2\x80\x9cInnocent?! You ba\xe2\x80\x94MPH!!!\xe2\x80\x9d</span> See, this is why you don\xe2\x80\x99t monologue. Wannabe freer of slaves just got a mouth full of tentacle, with the other two binding her in place. Level is important in this game, but skills and control are more important. This idiot hasn\xe2\x80\x99t even mastered silent casting, it seems, since no fire comes out when she struggles against the tentacles.<br />\xc2\xa0<br /><span style="color: #3366ff;">\xe2\x80\x9cYukiko, keep the three behind busy. Severa, help her out. Della, buff and heal them. Let me know if the cocky bitch gets free or starts using magic.\xe2\x80\x9d</span><br />\xc2\xa0<br /><span style="font-weight: bold;">\xe2\x80\x9c\xe2\x80\x9d\xe2\x80\x9dYes, Master!\xe2\x80\x9d\xe2\x80\x9d\xe2\x80\x9d</span> All three reply at once. Severa especially looks to be happy to have something to take her frustrations out on.<br />\xc2\xa0<br />I turn back to the four in front, and decide to make it quick, rather than play around. Don\xe2\x80\x99t give your enemies openings they can exploit! With a cry, I leap at the closest of the four and perform a beautiful iaijutsu slash, if I do say so myself. While the thieves may be a decent level, they\xe2\x80\x99re glass cannons, focusing mainly on DEX. The thief didn\xe2\x80\x99t even have time to know what happened, as his head separated from his body.<br />\xc2\xa0<br />The death broke the thieves\xe2\x80\x99 stupor at the sudden onslaught, and they began to attack. In the back, one of the thieves looked to be trying to free the sorceress, but unfortunately he was hampered by the presence of a dagger in his throat and kidney, care of Severa\xe2\x80\x99s de-stealthing form. The other two tried to get to her, but were blocked by Yukiko\xe2\x80\x99s blade, which took off one thief\xe2\x80\x99s arm in the first swing. The other managed to slip his blade into Yukiko\xe2\x80\x99s side, but the wound was healed almost instantly by Della.<br />\xc2\xa0<br />As for my three? Well, they were having even less fun than those guys. Instead of the Sun Blade, I held my Sacrificial Dagger in my off hand, and buried it in the chest of one of the thieves. I crouched into a spin, missing a sword aimed at my neck, and slashed out with Munsuraisa, taking out the remaining two at the knees. A moment later, each had been slain by the dagger. <br />\xc2\xa0<br />By the time I was finished, my pets had ended their play, as well, leaving only the sorceress to deal with. And I knew just what to do with HER! Reaching into my inventory, I pulled out one of the cheap copper chain necklaces I\xe2\x80\x99d stripped from the cultists, but never sold. The reason I never sold them was because they made good for nice, classy slave chokers. When I slipped the necklace around Zephara\xe2\x80\x99s neck, a flurry of messages appeared, as combat had ended.<br />\xc2\xa0<br /><div style="max-width: 100%; overflow:auto"><table><tbody><tr><td colspan='4'>From sacrificing your enemies, you gain 8 DEX!</td></tr></tbody></table></div><br /><br /><div style="max-width: 100%; overflow:auto"><table><tbody><tr><td colspan='4'>You have defeated Thief x7! You gain 800 XP!<br />You have defeated known outlaw Zephara Void! You gain 1000 XP!<br />You have defeated a target with a bounty on their head! You gain 500 GP!</td></tr></tbody></table></div><br /><br /><div style="max-width: 100%; overflow:auto"><table><tbody><tr><td colspan='4'>For enslaving a registered Adventurer, you gain 98 PP, 6 GP, 7 SP, and 5 CP from the enemy\xe2\x80\x99s Guild Card.</td></tr></tbody></table></div><br /><br /><div style="max-width: 100%; overflow:auto"><table><tbody><tr><td colspan='4'>For continuously enslaving, sacrificing, and eating people in a short time period, your alignment has changed to Chaotic Evil.</td></tr></tbody></table></div><br /><br />Smirking as I dismissed the windows, I looked at Zaphara, and with a snap of my fingers dismissed the tentacles. <span style="color: #3366ff;">\xe2\x80\x9cPoor Zaphara. Picked the wrong person to fight, didn\xe2\x80\x99t you?\xe2\x80\x9d</span><br />\xc2\xa0<br /><span style="color: #ff9933;">\xe2\x80\x9cYou BASTARD! I\xe2\x80\x99m going to kill you!\xe2\x80\x9d</span><br />\xc2\xa0<br /><span style="color: #3366ff;">\xe2\x80\x9cZephara, strip naked, and hand all your belongings to Della. I forbid you from logging out.\xe2\x80\x9d</span> Honestly, I wasn\xe2\x80\x99t sure whether that would work. Surely the company would have put in some kind of safeguard? Well, charm and enslavement magic does work on the character\xe2\x80\x99s mind, I\xe2\x80\x99d found that out from Yukiko already, so it just might keep a player from logging out. There\xe2\x80\x99d be the forced log out if they stayed on long enough to risk their health, but then they\xe2\x80\x99d still be in the same trouble once they logged back in. They would be forced to either live as a slave, make a new character, or quit the game entirely.<br />\xc2\xa0<br />Zephara kept up a constant stream of abuse as she got naked, but was unable to log out, even though I saw her trying to make the motions to press the button on her menu, but stopping herself each time. <span style="color: #3366ff;">\xe2\x80\x9cZephara, place your hands behind your head, fingers laced with one another.\xe2\x80\x9d</span> That shut her up as she was forced to present herself for the whole city.<span style="color: #3366ff;"> \xe2\x80\x9cNow, you\xe2\x80\x99ll be happy to know that this will be streaming very shortly. But for now, it seems I have more business before dinner. And do not speak until told otherwise.\xe2\x80\x9d</span><br />\xc2\xa0<br />When I led her to one of the local brothels, she looked panicked, and tried to beg as much as she could with her hands clasped behind her head and being unable to speak. This particular brothel enjoyed the patronage of many of the city guard. Given that she was a notorious outlaw who (until recently) had a high bounty on their head, she was sure to be popular. So I was happy to get another 50 GP for her.<br />\xc2\xa0<br />Della looked puzzled as we walked back to the inn for dinner. <span style="color: #ff3333;">\xe2\x80\x9cMaster, why didn\xe2\x80\x99t you just keep her, or at least rape her before selling her?\xe2\x80\x9d</span><br />\xc2\xa0<br /><span style="color: #3366ff;">\xe2\x80\x9cWell, unlike Yukiko here, I doubt she enjoys the thought of being a slave, especially as she was going around freeing slaves all over the place. Now, that wouldn\xe2\x80\x99t bother me, but Travelers can be an annoying bunch, especially when they\xe2\x80\x99re pissed off. So it would be more trouble than it was worth to keep her. Especially since once she is forced to return to the world we Travelers come from, she most likely won\xe2\x80\x99t be back, at least not in that form. She may still return to try and cause trouble, but it will take her a very long time to catch up and find us, and she\xe2\x80\x99ll be far weaker for it.\xe2\x80\x9d</span><br /><span style="color: #3366ff;">\xc2\xa0</span><br /><span style="color: #3366ff;">\xe2\x80\x9cAs for why I didn\xe2\x80\x99t rape her? I don\xe2\x80\x99t want to spoil the experience for her clients. You might not have noticed, but she probably wouldn\xe2\x80\x99t be quite the same after I took her.\xe2\x80\x9d</span><br />\xc2\xa0<br /><span style="color: #9966ff;">\xe2\x80\x9cYou\xe2\x80\x99re evil, Master!\xe2\x80\x9d</span> Yukiko giggled.<br />\xc2\xa0<br /><span style="color: #3366ff;">\xe2\x80\x9cActually, yeah. Seems all my killing, slaving, and sacrificing has caused my alignment to change. Go figure. Anyways, let\xe2\x80\x99s head back to the inn. That fight worked up an appetite.\xe2\x80\x9d</span><br /><br /><hr /><br />Zayn:<br /><div class='spoiler'><div class='smalltext' style='margin-bottom:2px'><b>Spoiler</b> : <input type='button' value='Show' class='spoilerButton'></div><div class='spoilerContent'><div style='display: none;'><br /><div style="max-width: 100%; overflow:auto"><table><tbody><tr><td>Name</td><td>Zayn Darkmore</td><td>Alignment</td><td>Chaotic Evil</td></tr><tr><td>Level</td><td>10</td><td>Race</td><td>Incubus</td></tr><tr><td>Class</td><td>Warlock</td><td>Sub-Class</td><td>None</td></tr><tr><td>Experience</td><td>47200/55000</td><td>Profession</td><td>Slave Trainer</td></tr><tr><td>HP</td><td>830/830</td><td>MP</td><td>1030/1230</td></tr><tr><td>HP Regen</td><td>8.3. per min</td><td>MP Regen</td><td>10.3 per min</td></tr><tr><td>Fame</td><td>1155</td><td>Infamy</td><td>420</td></tr><tr><td>105 PP</td><td>5 GP</td><td>3 SP</td><td>5 CP</td></tr><tr><td colspan='4'></td></tr><tr><td colspan='4'>Attributes</td></tr><tr><td>STR</td><td>69(79)</td><td>INT</td><td>73(103)</td></tr><tr><td>DEX</td><td>77(87)</td><td>WIS</td><td>69(