                        <div class="chapter-inner chapter-content">
            &lt;Zayn POV&gt;<br />It was nice learning more about my pets. That Severa was actually related to the royal family of Caledon was something to think on later. If my journeys took me that way, we\xe2\x80\x99d probably have to be careful. It would either make things easier, or much, much harder. Hard to tell.<br />\xc2\xa0<br />Anyways, the slave market! It was\xe2\x80\xa6 pretty much just like I expected it to be. Walking through the door, I was in a nicely appointed receiving room. The way the market worked is that you spoke with an \xe2\x80\x98agent\xe2\x80\x99 or \xe2\x80\x98hostess\xe2\x80\x99 while relaxing in a private room, and told them the requirements you wished for in a slave. Then they would go and bring in several slaves for you to pick from, and eventually you\xe2\x80\x99d narrow things down, and you could discuss price. There were two reasons for this. First, it meant they didn\xe2\x80\x99t have to have all their product on display all the time, which would drive down their living conditions. Second, it was the time honored tactic of drawing up the price once you hooked your customer on something they wanted.<br />\xc2\xa0<br />The hostess showed us into a private room, and I sat on a soft chair, and commanded my pets to kneel on either side of me. Part of this was for my own ego, naturally, but the main reason was theater. Framing the scene the way I wished, to elicit the proper responses both from the slaves, and from the slavers. If the slave reacted badly to my little harem, that told me something. Also, conveying to the slaver that I wasn\xe2\x80\x99t desperate would help keep the cost from getting out of hand.<br />\xc2\xa0<br />As a servant brought me a glass of wine, the hostess came in, and said,<span style="color: #669933;"> \xe2\x80\x9cWelcome to Zechariah\xe2\x80\x99s Slave Emporium!\xe2\x80\x9d</span> As she spoke, I took a moment to observe the woman. She was a shapely red-head, but I could see a slave collar on her. So a trusted slave in charge of sales? Well, sex sells, so I can see the point. <span style="color: #669933;">\xe2\x80\x9cWhat can we help you with today?\xe2\x80\x9d</span><br />\xc2\xa0<br /><span style="color: #3366ff;">\xe2\x80\x9cAh, first, I would like to gain training in the Slave Trainer profession. Second, I\xe2\x80\x99m an adventurer, and will be heading out on a long journey. As such, I would prefer to have an additional fighter in my company.\xe2\x80\x9d</span><br />\xc2\xa0<br /><span style="color: #669933;">\xe2\x80\x9cUnderstood. Would you prefer a male or female slave?\xe2\x80\x9d</span><br />\xc2\xa0<br /><span style="color: #3366ff;">\xe2\x80\x9cFemale.\xe2\x80\x9d</span><br />\xc2\xa0<br /><span style="color: #669933;">\xe2\x80\x9cAny other requirements?\xe2\x80\x9d</span><br />\xc2\xa0<br /><span style="color: #3366ff;">\xe2\x80\x9cI would prefer a warrior of some sort.\xe2\x80\x9d</span><br />\xc2\xa0<br /><span style="color: #669933;">\xe2\x80\x9cVery good. I will be back shortly with a selection.\xe2\x80\x9d</span> Bowing slightly, the hostess turned and left the room, her hips swaying seductively as she went. Yes, sex sells indeed. This Zachariah was a clever man.<br />\xc2\xa0<br />I sipped the wine carefully, not wishing it to go to my head. That wine was provided free of charge was yet another point showing that Zachariah knew his business. Before long, a man entered, and nodded to me. \xe2\x80\x9c<span style="color: #cc9933;">Ah, so you\xe2\x80\x99re the one Shelly told me about, hmm? Already got a start as a slave trainer, I see, but you need full training, then? Oh, and I\xe2\x80\x99m Zachariah, by the by.\xe2\x80\x9d</span><br />\xc2\xa0<br />I got up to offer the man my hand, with a respectful nod. <span style="color: #3366ff;">\xe2\x80\x9cA pleasure, sir. It would be my honor to learn the profession from one as obviously skilled as you are. I\xe2\x80\x99ve rarely seen a slave market so well run.\xe2\x80\x9d</span><br />\xc2\xa0<br /><span style="color: #cc9933;">\xe2\x80\x9cFlattery! But that won\xe2\x80\x99t get you a discount!\xe2\x80\x9d</span> Zachariah laughed, and then said, <span style="color: #cc9933;">\xe2\x80\x9cWell, the cost to train will be five silver. That won\xe2\x80\x99t be a problem, will it?\xe2\x80\x9d</span><br />\xc2\xa0<br /><span style="color: #3366ff;">\xe2\x80\x9cNot at all.\xe2\x80\x9d</span> I handed over the money obediently. No sense pissing off the people I needed things from. Being polite might get me a better deal, after all.<br /><br /><br /><div style="max-width: 100%; overflow:auto"><table><tbody><tr><td>Slave Trainer profession fully unlocked!<br />\xc2\xa0<br />Gain +10% to Training<br />Gain +15% to Whip Mastery<br />\xc2\xa0<br />Level 10: Obedience Training \xe2\x80\x93 Slaves under your command are more obedient, and better at following orders. Slaves are +10% to actions while following orders.</td></tr></tbody></table></div><br />\xc2\xa0<br />Hoh. So in addition to the other things, I got a bonus to my \xe2\x80\x98training\xe2\x80\x99 and \xe2\x80\x98whip\xe2\x80\x99 skills. Guess that made sense. That reminded me, that I\xe2\x80\x99d have to get a whip. Della already had one thanks to the gear we got from the Priestess, but I needed one of my own. More things to buy after getting a new slave. Ah well.<br />\xc2\xa0<br />While I waited, Zachariah and I chatted about things. Nothing world shaking, of course, but when he found I was a Traveler, we quickly began sharing information. General information about this world was of little value to him, while information about my world was of great value, since it would better allow him to hawk his wares to the Travelers coming in. Likewise, what I needed was information on this world. No contracts needed, or agreements struck, and I think we each profited more from the conversation than the other realized.<br />\xc2\xa0<br />Now the hostess returned, leading in a group of ten women, all clad in basic leather armor, gladiator style. There was a mix of races presented, including three humans, two dwarves, four beastkin (two tigers, a fox, and wolf), and a draconian! I observed them each.<br />\xc2\xa0<br /><div style="max-width: 100%; overflow:auto"><table><tbody><tr><td colspan='4'>Bruhiel Swiftblade<br />Human Female<br />Level 5 Fighter</td></tr></tbody></table></div><br /><div style="max-width: 100%; overflow:auto"><table><tbody><tr><td colspan='4'>Kiyabu Yukiko<br />Foxkin Female<br />Level 10 Samurai</td></tr></tbody></table></div><br /><div style="max-width: 100%; overflow:auto"><table><tbody><tr><td colspan='4'>Taryn Blackshield<br />Human Female<br />Level 1 Fighter</td></tr></tbody></table></div><br /><div style="max-width: 100%; overflow:auto"><table><tbody><tr><td colspan='4'>Bonnmyl Hammerfall<br />Dwarf Female<br />Level 50 Paladin (Defender)</td></tr></tbody></table></div><br /><div style="max-width: 100%; overflow:auto"><table><tbody><tr><td colspan='4'>Ember Swiftmane<br />Wolfkin Female<br />Level 3 Blackguard</td></tr></tbody></table></div><br /><div style="max-width: 100%; overflow:auto"><table><tbody><tr><td colspan='4'>Iraneth Blackscale<br />Draconian Female<br />Level 100 Barbarian (Tempest Fury)</td></tr></tbody></table></div><br /><div style="max-width: 100%; overflow:auto"><table><tbody><tr><td colspan='4'>Zenobia Lightmore<br />Human Female<br />Level 6 Paladin</td></tr></tbody></table></div><br /><div style="max-width: 100%; overflow:auto"><table><tbody><tr><td colspan='4'>Abyss Darkclaw<br />Tigerkin Female<br />Level 5 Fighter</td></tr></tbody></table></div><br /><div style="max-width: 100%; overflow:auto"><table><tbody><tr><td colspan='4'>Iris Darkclaw<br />Tigerkin Female<br />Level 5 Fighter</td></tr></tbody></table></div><br /><div style="max-width: 100%; overflow:auto"><table><tbody><tr><td colspan='4'>Runmira Stoutbrew<br />Dwarf Female<br />Level 15 Barbarian</td></tr></tbody></table></div><br />\xc2\xa0<br />I almost choked at a couple of the levels seen. Looking over to Zachariah, I said, <span style="color: #3366ff;">\xe2\x80\x9cI wonder, how did you come across that dwarf and the draconian? They seem awfully high leveled to be slaves.\xe2\x80\x9d</span><br />\xc2\xa0<br />Zachariah chuckled, and said, <span style="color: #cc9933;">\xe2\x80\x9cWell, I never bothered asking too closely, but it seems the dwarf has a bad habit. She gets preachy about the Light and all that if no one orders her to be silent. My personal guess is that someone slapped the collar on her to shut her up.\xe2\x80\x9d</span><br />\xc2\xa0<br />I laughed, and said, <span style="color: #3366ff;">\xe2\x80\x9cEven in another world, zealots will be zealots. And what of the draconian?\xe2\x80\x9d</span><br />\xc2\xa0<br /><span style="color: #cc9933;">\xe2\x80\x9cAh, well she is a special case. It seems she killed several noblemen\xe2\x80\x99s sons in a brawl. The courts sentenced her to slavery. Normally it would be death for something like that, but it seems one of the dead started it, so the judge gave her the option of slavery instead.\xe2\x80\x9d</span><br />\xc2\xa0<br />I nodded. Killing a person could get you in trouble, depending on who it was. Killing the sons of several noblemen? That was going to get you in deep, unless you did it somewhere out of sight, and disposed of the evidence. Just like in the real world. Killing a junky in the alley isn\xe2\x80\x99t going to get much attention from the cops. Killing the President\xe2\x80\x99s son in the middle of Times Square is going to get you killed, if you\xe2\x80\x99re lucky.<br />\xc2\xa0<br /><span style="color: #3366ff;">\xe2\x80\x9cAnd the two tigerkin? Are they sisters?\xe2\x80\x9d</span><br />\xc2\xa0<br /><span style="color: #cc9933;">\xe2\x80\x9cAh, good eye! Indeed they are. Unfortunately, their father was unable to pay his debts, and sold his daughters to make good. They can be sold singly or as a set, if you like.\xe2\x80\x9d</span><br />\xc2\xa0<br />Hmm. A set of tigerkin? That was certainly worth thinking about. But my eye returned to the Foxkin. That name and class\xe2\x80\xa6 nah, it couldn\xe2\x80\x99t be. <span style="color: #3366ff;">\xe2\x80\x9cAnd the fox?\xe2\x80\x9d</span><br />\xc2\xa0<br />The man\xe2\x80\x99s face fell. <span style="color: #cc9933;">\xe2\x80\x9cAh. A recent acquisition, and not quite tamed yet. She is a Traveler. I\xe2\x80\x99m not sure, but she may have offended one of the gods, as she suddenly appeared in the receiving room one day, with a collar already on her neck.\xe2\x80\x9d</span><br />\xc2\xa0<br /><span style="color: #3366ff;">\xe2\x80\x9cSo she isn\xe2\x80\x99t broken, yet?\xe2\x80\x9d</span><br />\xc2\xa0<br /><span style="color: #cc9933;">\xe2\x80\x9cNo, but you asked for warriors. Most of our slaves are here for other purposes.\xe2\x80\x9d</span><br />\xc2\xa0<br /><span style="color: #3366ff;">\xe2\x80\x9cOf course, of course. And what is the price on this foxkin?\xe2\x80\x9d</span><br />\xc2\xa0<br /><span style="color: #cc9933;">\xe2\x80\x9cIf she was fully trained, a Traveler sex slave collared with a collar that will remain with them even after they return from death would be worth at least a thousand gold. For a combat slave, at least a couple hundred. Untrained, however, and as a combat slave, I would say twenty gold, and I hold no responsibility for what happens after.\xe2\x80\x9d</span><br />\xc2\xa0<br /><span style="color: #3366ff;">\xe2\x80\x9cAnd the weapons and armor she appeared with?\xe2\x80\x9d</span><br />\xc2\xa0<br /><span style="color: #cc9933;">\xe2\x80\x9cIncluded, naturally.\xe2\x80\x9d</span><br />\xc2\xa0<br /><span style="color: #3366ff;">\xe2\x80\x9cHmm. Twenty is a little much for something like this, especially as I will have to train her while traveling the wilds. Ten gold.\xe2\x80\x9d</span><br />\xc2\xa0<br /><span style="color: #cc9933;">\xe2\x80\x9cOh, you jest, surely! A traveler\xe2\x80\x99s ability to resurrect from death is worth twice that, at least! Eighteen!\xe2\x80\x9d</span><br />\xc2\xa0<br />We haggled back and forth, and eventually settled on 15 GP, 3 SP, 5 CP. With that, I completed the process of transferring the slave collar\xe2\x80\x99s ownership over to myself, and I now had a new slave.<br />\xc2\xa0<br /><div class='spoiler'><div class='smalltext' style='margin-bottom:2px'><b>Spoiler</b> : <input type='button' value='Show' class='spoilerButton'></div><div class='spoilerContent'><div style='display: none;'><br /><div style="max-width: 100%; overflow:auto"><table><tbody><tr><td>Name</td><td>Kiyabu Yukiko</td><td>Alignment</td><td>Lawful Good</td></tr><tr><td>Level</td><td>10</td><td>Race</td><td>Foxkin</td></tr><tr><td>Class</td><td>Samurai</td><td>Sub-Class</td><td>None</td></tr><tr><td>Experience</td><td>45000/55000</td><td>Profession</td><td>Blacksmith</td></tr><tr><td>HP</td><td>1080/1080</td><td>MP</td><td>200/200</td></tr><tr><td>HP Regen</td><td>8.8 per min</td><td>MP Regen</td><td>2.0 per min</td></tr><tr><td>Fame</td><td>0</td><td>Infamy</td><td>0</td></tr><tr><td>0 PP</td><td>14 GP</td><td>32 SP</td><td>140 CP</td></tr><tr><td colspan='4'></td></tr><tr><td colspan='4'>Attributes</td></tr><tr><td>STR</td><td>74</td><td>INT</td><td>20</td></tr><tr><td>DEX</td><td>74</td><td>WIS</td><td>20</td></tr><tr><td>CON</td><td>88</td><td>CHA</td><td>20</td></tr><tr><td>Luck</td><td>0</td><td>Attack</td><td>+30</td></tr><tr><td>Defense</td><td>+50</td><td>???</td><td></td></tr><tr><td colspan='4'>Points Remaining: 0</td></tr><tr><td colspan='4'></td></tr><tr><td colspan='1'>Titles</td><td colspan='3'>Slave</td></tr><tr><td colspan='4'></td></tr><tr><td colspan='4'>Resistances</td></tr><tr><td>Pierce</td><td>+30%</td><td>Bludgeoning</td><td>+30%</td></tr><tr><td>Slash</td><td>+30%</td><td>Fire</td><td></td></tr><tr><td>Ice</td><td></td><td>Water</td><td></td></tr><tr><td>Lightning</td><td></td><td>Wind</td><td></td></tr><tr><td>Earth</td><td></td><td>Light</td><td></td></tr><tr><td>Dark</td><td></td><td>Charm</td><td></td></tr><tr><td colspan='4'>Enslaved to Zayn Darkmore \xe2\x80\x93 Compelled to follow all commands.</td></tr><tr><td>Diety</td><td colspan='3'>Tempus</td></tr><tr><td colspan='4'></td></tr><tr><td colspan='4'>Proficiencies</td></tr><tr><td colspan='4'>Simple Weapons<br />Martial Weapons<br />Shields<br />Swords<br />Bows<br />Light Armor<br />Medium Armor<br />Heavy Armor</td></tr><tr><td colspan='4'></td></tr><tr><td colspan='4'>Qualities</td></tr><tr><td colspan='4'>Hurts so Good<br />Senpai Noticed Me!<br />Art of the Forge<br />The Story of O<br />Lady Luck\xe2\x80\x99s Fool<br />Gullible\xe2\x80\x99s Travels</td></tr><tr><td colspan='4'></td></tr><tr><td colspan='4'>Skills</td></tr><tr><td colspan='4'>Foxfire - Beginner 2 (0%)<br />Blacksmith - Basic 3 (0%)<br />Sword Mastery - Basic 1 (0%)<br />Sneak - Beginner 1 (10%)<br />Move Silently - Beginner 1 (10%)<br />Identify - Beginner 2 (18%)<br />Observe - Beginner 2 (75%)<br />Bow\xc2\xa0Mastery - Beginner 3 (0%)<br />Taunt - Beginner 4 (0%)<br />Parry - Beginner 6 (0%)<br />[tr][td4]</td></tr><tr><td colspan='4'>Class Benefits</td></tr><tr><td colspan='4'>+20% with Swords<br />+20 HP per Level<br />All Armor Proficiency<br />Bows Proficiency<br />Swords Proficiency<br />Skills added<br />\xc2\xa0<br />Level 10: Iaijutsu</td></tr><tr><td colspan='4'>Sub-class Benefits</td></tr><tr><td colspan='4'></td></tr><tr><td colspan='4'>Profession Benefits</td></tr><tr><td colspan='4'>Blacksmith<br />+30% Fire Resistance<br />Increased quality of works<br />Increased speed of production<br />+15% to Identify weapons and armor<br />\xc2\xa0<br />Level 10 \xe2\x80\x93 Imbue Armor</td></tr><tr><td colspan='4'>Perks</td></tr><tr><td colspan='4'>Able Learner<br />Strength Focus<br />Dexterity Focus<br />Constitution Focus<br />Improved Race</td></tr></tbody></table></div><br />\xc2\xa0</div></div></div><br />\xc2\xa0<br />While I was looking over Yukiko\xe2\x80\x99s stats, I saw another window pop up.<br />\xc2\xa0<br /><div style="max-width: 100%; overflow:auto"><table><tbody><tr><td colspan='4'>For purchasing another Traveler as a slave, you gain the title Chainmaker.<br />For being the first Traveler to own another Traveler, the title is upgraded to Master Chainmaker.<br />+525 Fame (Increased from 500)<br />+5 to all stats for each slave owned.<br />Slaves gain +10 to all stats.</td></tr></tbody></table></div>
        </div>
